        We selected three groups of patients: Hemodialysis group, peritoneal dialysis group and the
        group with stage 4 chronic kidney disease. A control group was formed from healthy
        volunteers also.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  hemodialysis and peritoneal dialysis patients who had been on dialysis therapy for
             more than 3 months,

          -  age between 18-80 years,

          -  patients with creatinine clearance between 15-30 ml/min.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age less than 18 or more than 80,

          -  diabetic patients,

          -  current active infectious or inflammatory disease.
      </textblock>
